
[1]deify

   DEIFY, v.t. [L. A god, and to make.]

   1. To make a god; to exalt to the rank of a heathen deity; to enroll
   among the deities; as, Julius Cesar was deified.

   2. To exalt into an object of worship; to treat as an object of supreme
   regard; as a covetous man deifies his treasures.

   3. To exalt to a deity in estimation; to reverence or praise as a
   deity.

   The pope was formerly extolled and deified by his votaries.
